issue_body:
Installation via `pip` under cygwin puts some files into locations where they cannot be found by corresponding tools. In particular:

* All XSLT stylesheets are in `$CYGWIN_ROOT/lib\python2.7\site-packages\pyang-1.6-py2.7.egg\share\yang\xslt\`;

* bash completion script is in `$CYGWIN_ROOT/lib\python2.7\site-packages\pyang-1.6-py2.7.egg/etc`.

I'm not sure what the motivation is for putting them where they are in view.html. Maybe there is one. However, if you want to use require.js, it will break if included in the current locations. 

On the other hand, it will work if those are moved to end of head element, as in:

    		</script>
    		{{custom_head}}
    		<script type='text/javascript'>
    		    	{{custom_js}}
    	    	</script>
    	</head>

which can then be used with:

       def getCustomHead(self):
            return """
               <script src="http://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/require.js/2.1.16/require.js"></script>
               """

        def getCustomJS(self):
            return """
                require.config({
                    paths: {
                        ...
                    }
                });
                """
etc.

Even when using the exact sample provided in the docs.

````json
{
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "additionalProperties": {
                "anyOf": [
                    {"type": "string"},
                    {"type": "number"},
                    {"type": "null"}
                ]
            }
        }
    }
}
````

